---
const SITE_NAME = "The-Circle";
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>League Rules • {SITE_NAME}</title>
    <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.png" type="image/svg+xml">
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="The-Circle League rules, policies, roster settings, and scoring."
    />
  </head>

  <body>
    <div class="page">
      <header class="top">
        <div class="container nav">
          <a class="brand" href="/">
            <span class="mark" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span class="name">{SITE_NAME}</span>
          </a>

          <nav class="links">
            <a href="/discord">Discord</a>
            <a href="/league">League</a>
            <a href="/about">About</a>

          </nav>


        </div>
      </header>

      <main class="container">
        <section class="hero">
          <div class="welcome">
            <h1>League Rules & Settings</h1>
            <p class="sub">
              This page is the “source of truth” for how the league is run: expectations, policies, roster settings,
              and scoring. It’s meant to keep things fair and keep the season moving.
            </p>
            <p class="fine">
              Quick nav:
              <a class="jump" href="#policies">Policies</a> ·
              <a class="jump" href="#conduct">Conduct</a> ·
              <a class="jump" href="#communication">Communication</a> ·
              <a class="jump" href="#trophy">Trophy</a> ·
              <a class="jump" href="#league-size">League Size</a> ·
              <a class="jump" href="#commissioner">Commissioner</a> ·
              <a class="jump" href="#roster">Roster</a> ·
              <a class="jump" href="#scoring">Scoring</a>
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="card" id="policies">
          <h2>Policies</h2>

          <div class="stack">
            <div class="ruleBlock">
              <h3>Inactive manager policy</h3>
              <ul>
                <li><strong>Inactive Team Identification:</strong> A team is considered inactive if no lineup changes are made for <strong>two consecutive weeks</strong> without prior notice to the Commissioner.</li>
                <li><strong>Auto-Lineup Setup:</strong> If a manager is inactive, the Commissioner reserves the right to set the team’s lineup using the <strong>highest projected players</strong>.</li>
                <li><strong>Chronic Inactivity:</strong> Persistent inactivity without communication may result in the team being <strong>permanently removed</strong> from the league.</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="note">Goal: keep weekly matchups fair for everyone.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="ruleBlock">
              <h3>Penalty policy</h3>
              <ul>
                <li><strong>First offense:</strong> Written warning from the Commissioner.</li>
                <li><strong>Second offense:</strong> Roster lock for one week.</li>
                <li><strong>Third offense:</strong> Possible removal from the league, based on a league vote.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="ruleBlock">
              <h3>Manager replacement policy</h3>
              <ul>
                <li><strong>Finding a replacement:</strong> The Commissioner will work to find a new manager to take over the team.</li>
                <li><strong>Interim management:</strong> Until a replacement is found, the Commissioner may set lineups or freeze the team to ensure fairness.</li>
                <li><strong>Keeper eligibility:</strong> Teams managed by a replacement manager remain eligible for keepers or prizes.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="ruleBlock">
              <h3>Dispute resolution policy</h3>
              <ul>
                <li><strong>Initial review:</strong> Disputes should be submitted to the Commissioner in writing, including the issue and suggested resolution.</li>
                <li><strong>League vote:</strong> If unresolved, disputes may be put to a league-wide vote. A majority decision is final.</li>
                <li><strong>Appeals:</strong> Once a decision is made, it cannot be appealed further within the same season.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="card" id="conduct">
          <h2>Conduct guidelines</h2>
          <p class="note">
            Trash talk is fine. Being a problem isn’t. Keep it fun and keep it readable.
          </p>

          <div class="grid2">
            <div class="tile">
              <h3>Active participation</h3>
              <p>Set your lineup weekly to ensure fair competition.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tile">
              <h3>Respectful communication</h3>
              <p>No personal attacks, discrimination, or harassment.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tile">
              <h3>Fair play</h3>
              <p>No collusion or intentional actions that compromise league integrity.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tile">
              <h3>Sportsmanship</h3>
              <p>Win without rubbing it in. Lose without melting down.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p class="fine">
            Violations may result in warnings, lineup adjustments, roster locks, or removal at the Commissioner’s discretion.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="card" id="communication">
          <h2>Communication policy</h2>

          <div class="ruleBlock">
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Primary platform:</strong> League communications are conducted via Discord.</li>
              <li><strong>Response expectations:</strong> Managers are expected to respond to Commissioner or league-wide messages within <strong>3 days</strong>.</li>
              <li><strong>Notification of absence:</strong> Managers should notify the Commissioner if they plan to be unavailable for an extended period (vacation, work travel, etc.).</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="card" id="trophy">
          <h2>League trophy policy</h2>

          <div class="ruleBlock">
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Responsibility:</strong> The winner is responsible for keeping the trophy safe, clean, and in good condition while in their possession.</li>
              <li><strong>Damage or loss:</strong> If the trophy is damaged or lost while in the winner’s care, they are liable for the full cost of repair or replacement.</li>
              <li><strong>Transfer of trophy:</strong> The trophy must be returned to the Commissioner before the start of the next season.</li>
              <li><strong>Display:</strong> The trophy may be displayed at the winner’s discretion, provided it remains protected from potential harm.</li>
              <li><strong>Acknowledgment:</strong> By accepting the trophy, the winner agrees to these terms.</li>
            </ul>

            <p class="note">
              Failure to comply may result in penalties, including forfeiture of future eligibility to hold the trophy.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="card" id="league-size">
          <h2>Expansion / contraction policy</h2>

          <div class="ruleBlock">
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Adding teams:</strong> Expansion can only occur in the offseason, with majority approval of current managers.</li>
              <li><strong>Reducing teams:</strong> If participation decreases, the league may contract with a majority vote. Managers of removed teams will be refunded entry fees (if applicable).</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="card" id="commissioner">
          <h2>Commissioner transition policy</h2>

          <div class="ruleBlock">
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Proposal for vote:</strong> Any league member can propose a change in Commissioner by submitting a formal request to the current Commissioner and notifying all league members.</li>
              <li><strong>Vote of confidence:</strong> A vote will be held among all league members. At least <strong>75%</strong> of active members must agree for the change to be implemented.</li>
              <li><strong>Transition period:</strong> The outgoing Commissioner assists the incoming Commissioner during a <strong>two-week</strong> transition period to transfer settings, responsibilities, and league materials.</li>
              <li><strong>New Commissioner expectations:</strong> The incoming Commissioner commits to maintaining league integrity, enforcing rules, and keeping the league enjoyable.</li>
              <li><strong>Re-election option:</strong> The league may review the Commissioner role at the end of each season.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="card" id="roster">
          <h2>Roster settings</h2>

          <div class="ruleBlock">
            <h3>Starting positions</h3>
            <ul class="cols">
              <li><strong>QB:</strong> 1</li>
              <li><strong>WR:</strong> 2</li>
              <li><strong>RB:</strong> 2</li>
              <li><strong>TE:</strong> 1</li>
              <li><strong>Flex (WR/RB/TE):</strong> 1</li>
              <li><strong>K:</strong> 1</li>
              <li><strong>DEF:</strong> 1</li>
              <li><strong>Bench:</strong> 6</li>
              <li><strong>IR:</strong> 2</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="card" id="scoring">
          <h2>Scoring rules</h2>

          <div class="stack">
            <div class="ruleBlock">
              <h3>Offense</h3>
              <ul>
                <li><strong>Passing yards:</strong> 1 point per 25 yards</li>
                <li><strong>Passing TD:</strong> 4 points</li>
                <li><strong>Interceptions:</strong> -1 point</li>
                <li><strong>Rushing yards:</strong> 1 point per 10 yards</li>
                <li><strong>Rushing TD:</strong> 6 points</li>
                <li><strong>Receptions:</strong> 0.5 points (Half-PPR)</li>
                <li><strong>Receiving yards:</strong> 1 point per 10 yards</li>
                <li><strong>Receiving TD:</strong> 6 points</li>
                <li><strong>Fumbles lost:</strong> -2 points</li>
                <li><strong>2-point conversions:</strong> 2 points</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="ruleBlock">
              <h3>Kickers</h3>
              <ul>
                <li><strong>FG 0–19:</strong> 3 points</li>
                <li><strong>FG 20–29:</strong> 3 points</li>
                <li><strong>FG 30–39:</strong> 3 points</li>
                <li><strong>FG 40–49:</strong> 4 points</li>
                <li><strong>FG 50+:</strong> 5 points</li>
                <li><strong>XP made:</strong> 1 point</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="ruleBlock">
              <h3>Defense / Special Teams</h3>
              <ul>
                <li><strong>Sack:</strong> 1 point</li>
                <li><strong>Interception:</strong> 2 points</li>
                <li><strong>Fumble recovery:</strong> 2 points</li>
                <li><strong>Defensive TD:</strong> 6 points</li>
                <li><strong>Safety:</strong> 2 points</li>
                <li><strong>Blocked kick:</strong> 2 points</li>
                <li><strong>Kickoff/punt return TD:</strong> 6 points</li>
              </ul>

              <h3 style="margin-top:14px;">Points allowed</h3>
              <ul class="cols">
                <li><strong>0:</strong> 10</li>
                <li><strong>1–6:</strong> 7</li>
                <li><strong>7–13:</strong> 4</li>
                <li><strong>14–20:</strong> 1</li>
                <li><strong>21–27:</strong> 0</li>
                <li><strong>28–34:</strong> -1</li>
                <li><strong>35+:</strong> -4</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p class="fine">
            If the host platform settings ever differ from this page, the league should update one of them so they match.
          </p>
        </section>
      </main>

      <footer class="footer">
        <div class="container foot">
          <span>© {new Date().getFullYear()} {SITE_NAME}</span>
          <span class="muted">Official League Rules</span>
        </div>
      </footer>
    </div>

    <style is:global>
      html, body { height: 100%; }

      body{
        margin:0;
        min-height:100vh;
        font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, Segoe UI, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif;
        color: rgba(255,255,255,0.92);

        background-image:
          radial-gradient(900px 500px at 15% 10%, rgba(9,255,3,0.14), transparent 60%),
          radial-gradient(800px 450px at 85% 15%, rgba(120,170,255,0.18), transparent 55%),
          radial-gradient(700px 450px at 55% 95%, rgba(255,170,120,0.10), transparent 55%),
          linear-gradient(#070a0f, #070a0f);

        background-repeat:no-repeat;
        background-size:100% 100%;
        background-attachment:fixed;
      }

      a{ color:inherit; text-decoration:none; }
      .container{ max-width: 1020px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 18px; }

      .page{ min-height:100vh; display:flex; flex-direction:column; }
      main{ flex:1; }

      /* Top nav */
      .top{
        position: sticky;
        top: 0;
        z-index: 10;
        backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
        background: rgba(7,10,15,0.55);
        border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.10);
      }

      .nav{
        display:flex;
        align-items:center;
        justify-content:space-between;
        padding:14px 18px;
        gap:14px;
      }

      .brand{
        display:flex;
        align-items:center;
        gap:10px;
        font-weight:900;
        letter-spacing:-0.02em;
        white-space:nowrap;
      }

      .mark{
        width:12px;
        height:12px;
        border-radius:999px;
        background:#09ff03;
        box-shadow:
          0 0 0 6px rgba(9,255,3,0.12),
          0 0 28px rgba(9,255,3,0.25);
      }

      .links{ display:flex; gap:14px; align-items:center; }
      .links a{ color: rgba(255,255,255,0.78); font-size:14px; }
      .links a:hover{ color: rgba(255,255,255,0.95); }

      .pill{
        padding:10px 12px;
        border-radius:999px;
        border: 1px solid rgba(9,255,3,0.24);
        background: rgba(9,255,3,0.10);
        color: rgba(255,255,255,0.95);
        box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px rgba(9,255,3,0.08) inset;
      }

      .mobileJoin{ display:none; }

      /* Hero */
      .hero{ padding: 34px 0 10px; }

      .welcome{
        border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12);
        border-radius: 22px;
        background: rgba(255,255,255,0.06);
        box-shadow: 0 24px 70px rgba(0,0,0,0.45);
        padding: 22px;
      }

      h1{
        margin: 0 0 10px;
        font-size: 44px;
        letter-spacing: -0.03em;
        line-height: 1.1;
      }

      .sub{
        margin: 0;
        color: rgba(255,255,255,0.74);
        font-size: 16px;
        line-height: 1.7;
        max-width: 92ch;
      }

      .fine{
        margin-top: 10px;
        color: rgba(255,255,255,0.55);
        font-size: 13px;
      }

      .jump{
        color: rgba(255,255,255,0.78);
        border-bottom: 1px dashed rgba(255,255,255,0.22);
      }
      .jump:hover{ color: rgba(255,255,255,0.95); }

      /* Cards */
      .card{
        margin: 18px 0;
        border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12);
        background: rgba(255,255,255,0.06);
        border-radius: 20px;
        padding: 20px;
        box-shadow: 0 20px 60px rgba(0,0,0,0.45);
      }

      h2{ margin: 0 0 10px; font-size: 22px; letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
      h3{ margin: 0 0 8px; font-size: 16px; }

      .note{
        margin: 8px 0 0;
        color: rgba(255,255,255,0.70);
        line-height: 1.6;
      }

      .ruleBlock{
        border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12);
        border-radius: 18px;
        padding: 16px;
        background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
      }

      ul{ margin: 10px 0 0; padding-left: 18px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.78); line-height: 1.65; }
      li{ margin: 6px 0; }
      strong{ color: rgba(255,255,255,0.92); }

      .stack{ display:grid; gap: 12px; margin-top: 10px; }

      .grid2{
        display:grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0,1fr));
        gap: 12px;
        margin-top: 12px;
      }

      .tile{
        border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12);
        border-radius: 18px;
        padding: 16px;
        background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
      }

      .tile p{ margin: 6px 0 0; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.72); line-height: 1.6; }

      .cols{
        display:grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0,1fr));
        gap: 4px 18px;
        padding-left: 18px;
      }

      /* Footer */
      .footer{
        border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.10);
        background: rgba(7,10,15,0.35);
        backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
      }

      .foot{
        display:flex;
        justify-content:space-between;
        gap:12px;
        padding: 16px 18px;
        flex-wrap:wrap;
      }

      .muted{ color: rgba(255,255,255,0.55); }

      @media (max-width: 980px){
        .grid2{ grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
        .cols{ grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      }

      @media (max-width: 820px){
        .links{ display:none; }
        .mobileJoin{ display:inline-flex; }
      }
    </style>
  </body>
</html>
